Job Title: Senior Commercial Analyst - Global Retail Org.
Ad Text:
About the Role:
Our client is a global Retail organisation with a range of iconic, household  brands and who have been regarded as an "Employer of Choice" in the Retail / FMCG sector. This Senior Commercial Analyst is a newly-created, career-defining role which will help provide insightful analysis into key performance trends that exist in order to drive the positive financial direction of the company. Furthermore, you will be acting as the "go-to" commercial finance business partner for the GM's of Sales, Operations & Customer Support; translating financial data into actionable business insights. This opportunity is a permanent full-time role.


Key Responsibilities:
Act as the "go-to" Finance Business Partner to a number of GM's; providing them with timely reports and insights. 
Lead KPI reporting for large operational divisions 
Make recommendations to support the business based on actual data, analysis and insights
Contribute to month-end close reporting
Analyse and explain all cost elements with regards to margin for actual results, forecast or budgeted performance
Conduct scenario analysis to evaluate commercial risks and opportunities
Analyse market, competitor, and internal performance data to deliver commercial insights
Prepare and maintain dashboards and reports (including KPIs)
Assist with the construction of the forecast, budget and 5 year plan from gross sales to gross margin
Skills and Experience:
CA or CPA qualified or working towards.
Ideally proven working experience in a tangible product industry. (i.e. Retail, FMCG, Pharmaceutical, etc.)
Extensive Finance Business Partnering experience 
Full PnL ownership in past roles desirable
Strong proficiency in advanced Microsoft Excel modelling
Experience working with large datasets and data manipulation
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
Strong stakeholder management and communication skills
Ability to work independently and manage multiple priorities
What's in it for you?

Work for a Global market-leader in the Retail sector who have been recognised as an "Employer of Choice"
Genuine internal career progression opportunites; report to an impressive Head of FP&A and work closely with an accomplished CFO.
North Ryde office with hybrid working, proximity to metro station and  free parking available

We are partnering with a large NFP organisation who provide crucial services to the community, to recruit an Investment Analyst for a 12-month fixed term contract. This is a unique chance to join a purpose-driven organisation undergoing transformation and growth, ideal for someone who thrives in commercial analysis, strategic finance, and executive level collaboration.

The Opportunity
Reporting to the CFO, you will play a key role in evaluating strategic investments, supporting M&A activity, driving long-term financial planning, and delivering insights that shape enterprise decisions.  You will work closely with executives, operational leaders, and external partners on initiatives that strengthen financial performance and advance the organisation’s mission.

Key Responsibilities
Analyse business cases using NPV, IRR, ROI, break-even analysis, sensitivity testing and 5-year scenario modelling
Develop, maintain and enhance long-term forecasting frameworks, including capital and cost-allocation models
Assess major strategic opportunities, including financial modelling, valuations, and due diligence
Undertake commercial viability assessments and partner with internal/external stakeholders to support negotiations
Contribute to financial turnaround initiatives, cost efficiency programs and strategic restructuring
Prepare high-quality investment papers, Board reports, Steer-Co updates and executive briefing notes
Provide actionable insights that support capital allocation, pricing decisions, and organisational strategy
Build trusted relationships across the organisation, acting as a commercial and financial business partner
Monitor market trends, risks and financial performance to inform strategic decision-making
About You
You will bring a blend of technical financial capability, commercial acumen and strong communication skills. Ideally, you have experience in:
Investment analysis, corporate finance, commercial modelling or FP&A
Building advanced financial models (Excel, scenario modelling, valuations)
Partnering with senior stakeholders and presenting complex information clearly
Working in large, complex organisations - experience in NFP, infrastructure, healthcare, or consulting highly regarded
Qualified finance professional (CA/CPA/CFA/CIMA)

Company: Laing O'Rourke Australia Construction Pty Limited
Ad Text:
About Laing O'Rourke

Laing O’Rourke is a $6 billion international operation with 70 years of involvement in Australian construction and infrastructure, including nearly two decades under the Laing O’Rourke banner. The business delivers projects as diverse as the environments in which they are built, from high security military bases and major rail transport infrastructure projects, through to landmark buildings at the transport interface. Laing O’Rourke owns one of Australia’s largest plant and equipment hire company called Select Plant Australia. We know the right culture combined with purposeful technology will help us meet demand and deliver certainty for our clients. That’s the #powerofexperience.



About the role

We are currently seeking a Solutions Delivery Lead for our AI-driven intelligence services business. The position could be based in Sydney or Melbourne. This role offers great career prospects with a privately-owned tier 1 constructor and international engineering enterprise.

In this role, you will lead client engagements from initiation through delivery to deliver high-quality, data-driven insights that transform project outcomes. You will operate as a trusted advisor to clients whilst coordinating with internal technical specialists to solve complex projects in construction, mining, and infrastructure.



Key responsibilities

Lead 2-3 concurrent client projects (typically duration of 3-4 months)
Manage project scope, timeline, quality and stakeholder expectations
Translate technical optimisation outputs to business value
Apply logical frameworks and data-driven analysis to generate insights
Break down complex, ambiguous problems into structured work plans
Lead stakeholder interviews and discovery workshops
Contribute to service design and methodology refinement
Scope new opportunities and develop project approaches
Contribute to proposal development and pitch preparation


About you

Minimum 4 years' experience in management consulting
Tertiary degree in relevant field. MBA or postgraduate qualification is desirable but not required
Experience in managing similar projects with proven track of leading engagements independently
End to end delivery experience from scoping through to final recommendations
Data and insight generation analytical skills
Experience in construction or mining sector is preferred but not essential


Benefits

We work hard to create an environment that brings out the best in our people. We believe in building careers through providing a safe, connected and innovative culture that supports ongoing growth and development. We offer industry-leading benefits such as specialised learning and development programs, a mental health and wellbeing program, industry leading paid parental leave policy, an additional purchased leave option and coaching programs for staff on parental leave.


Diversity & Inclusion

We are committed to building a workforce that reflects the diverse society in which we live and work. Laing O’Rourke is proud to hold the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) Citation - Employer of Choice for Gender Equality.

Laing O'Rourke actively supports a diverse workforce and strongly encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples and people from culturally diverse backgrounds. Download our Stretch Reconciliation Action Plan at https://www.laingorourke.com/company/diversity-and-inclusion

Ad Text:
Company Description

KPMG is one of the most trusted and respected global professional services firms. Through depth of expertise, clarity of insight and strength of purpose we help our clients solve complex challenges, steer change, strengthen, transition and grow. We are looking for talented people who share our purpose of inspiring confidence and empowering change for our clients, our people and our communities.

KPMG ThinkPay offers a multi-disciplinary team combining specialist capability across Risk, Assurance, Workplace Relations Advisory, Employment Law, Tax and Data Analytics all in one place. By drawing on our subject matter experts, KPMG is uniquely positioned to help you navigate the complexities of your payroll environment.

Job Description

With continued growth, we are looking to recruit an experienced Director to join our ThinkPay team. This is a senior leadership role responsible for shaping and delivering high-impact advisory solutions, driving innovation, and building trusted client relationships across complex payroll and workforce compliance matters.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead the strategic direction and delivery of large-scale consulting engagements across payroll remediation, workforce compliance, and data-driven risk management.

Oversee multidisciplinary teams, fostering a high-performance culture and mentoring future leaders.

Drive business development initiatives, contributing to market growth and client acquisition.

Ensure quality, compliance, and excellence across all engagements, with a focus on sustainable outcomes.

How are you extraordinary?
You are a strategic thinker with a passion for solving complex problems through data, technology, and advisory excellence. You bring:

Deep expertise in data analytics, including cleansing, modelling, and insight generation.

Advanced proficiency in SQL and Python; experience with Azure and cloud-based analytics platforms is highly regarded.

Proven track record in leading remediation programs and managing large-scale projects.

Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence at senior levels.

Experience in a Big 4, mid-tier, or boutique consulting firm, or in a senior data or compliance role within a large organisation.

Qualifications

STEM degree in Science, Technology, Engineering or Mathematics.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Company Description

KPMG is one of the most trusted and respected global professional services firms. Through depth of expertise, clarity of insight and strength of purpose we help our clients solve complex challenges, steer change, strengthen, transition and grow. We are looking for talented people who share our purpose of inspiring confidence and empowering change for our clients, our people and our communities.

KPMG ThinkPay offers a multi-disciplinary team combining specialist capability across Risk, Assurance, Workplace Relations Advisory, Employment Law, Tax and Data Analytics all in one place. By drawing on our subject matter experts, KPMG is uniquely positioned to help you navigate the complexities of your payroll environment.

Job Description

Due to continued growth, we are seeking an experienced Associate Director to join our ThinkPay team. This is a leadership role that will see you managing high-impact consulting engagements and guiding clients through complex payroll and workforce compliance challenges.

Key Responsibilities

Lead and deliver complex consulting engagements across data analytics, payroll remediation, workforce compliance.

Act as a trusted advisor to clients, managing relationships and providing strategic insights.

Drive risk management and remediation programs with a focus on quality and impact.

Mentor and lead multidisciplinary teams, fostering capability and professional growth.

How are you extraordinary?

You are a strategic thinker and problem solver with a passion for delivering value through data and advisory services. You bring:

Strong data analytics skills, including cleansing, modelling, and insights generation.

Advanced proficiency in SQL and Python; experience with Azure and cloud-based analytics platforms is highly regarded.

Strong project management skills, ideally with experience in remediation programs.

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement capabilities.

Proven experience in data analytics, payroll remediation, workforce compliance, or broader consulting.

Background in a Big 4, mid-tier, or boutique consulting firm, or experience in data teams within large organisations.

Qualifications

STEM degree in the field of Science, Technology, Engineering or Mathematics.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Salary: Our people build skills for the future

Job Description

With continued growth, we are looking to recruit an experienced Manager to join our ThinkPay team.

As a valued member of the KPMG ThinkPay team, you will have accountability for:

Delivering leading edge data analytics and remediation activities leveraging specialist knowledge of different payroll and HR systems.

Contributing data-driven insights to help our make important business decisions and minimise risks around employee entitlements.

Collaborating with a team of multi-disciplinary specialists, including legal, systems, governance and risk consulting and behavioural risk, to bring fit-for-purpose solutions.

You are someone with:

Experience in client relationship management

Head of HR | Critical portfolio 300 FTE and growing
High-impact role in a complex, highly regulated environment
Enterprise-wide influence | Infrastructure sector
Major Projects experience 
Drive strategic workforce planning, cultural evolution, and risk mitigation
Sydney CBD | Hybrid working available 
MUST have critical infrastructure experience - Construction | Rail | Engineering | Mining
Our client is seeking a confident, strategic, and influential HR leader to join a high-performing business at the forefront of critical infrastructure projects. This is not a transactional role, it requires deep expertise across the employee lifecycle, with a focus on strategic workforce planning, organisational design, ER/IR risk management, and futureproofing the business through talent pipelines and cultural transformation.

This position will suit someone with strong commercial and regulatory acumen, who brings experience in high-value project environments, is confident navigating complex stakeholder dynamics, and has a systemic mindset to influence and embed best practice across the enterprise.

You will work closely with executive and project leadership teams on a growing portfolio expected to scale in headcount. Success in this role requires a high degree of emotional intelligence, the ability to read the environment, pre-empt issues, and bring people on the journey, particularly in a high-pressure, delivery-focused setting.

Key Responsibilities:

Strategic HR Leadership

Act as a senior advisor and critical partner to business and project leaders
Lead the development and implementation of integrated people strategies aligned to business growth and transformation priorities
Partner with Centres of Excellence (e.g. Talent, L&D, Reward, Operations) to drive consistency and alignment across the operating model
Embed workforce planning as a strategic discipline – from ramp-up and resourcing to cost forecasting, risk mitigation, and future workforce dispersion
Talent, Capability & Risk

Build and execute robust bench strength, talent pipelines and succession plans that meet current and future technical demands
Champion strategic approaches to performance, capability development, and leadership growth
Understand and proactively manage ER/IR risks with a focus on business continuity, regulatory compliance and cultural integrity
Coach and influence senior stakeholders on systemic and sustainable people practices
Workforce Planning & Project Alignment

Deeply understand project lifecycles, technical workforce needs, and the rhythm of ramp-up/down phases
Partner with project leaders to develop real-time workforce planning and cost forecasting tools
Monitor workforce engagement, burnout risks and leadership gaps. Proactively engage with Directors to ensure team resilience and readiness
Drive strategic decision-making through people analytics and insights
Culture, Engagement & Change

Champion a positive, inclusive, high-performance culture
Design and execute cultural initiatives and engagement strategies tailored to a project-heavy environment
Lead large-scale change management initiatives and guide teams through complexity and transformation
Run engagement surveys, interpret results, and implement actions that create lasting impact
About You:

Degree qualified in HR, Business, Psychology or related field (postgrad/MBA desirable)
7–10+ years’ Senior HR experience, including significant time in strategic HRBP or HR leadership roles
Proven experience working in complex, regulated and infrastructure environments
Deep understanding of project lifecycles, workforce phasing, and talent implications
Strong ER/IR expertise with a commercial and risk lens
A natural influencer and coach, with high EQ and ability to lead through ambiguity
Demonstrated experience in leading cultural transformation and capability building
Strong analytical skills, with ability to translate data into strategic insight and action
What’s On Offer:

Influence and shape the people agenda in a high-growth portfolio
Work alongside senior leaders committed to transformation and excellence
A collaborative, values-led environment with hybrid working flexibility
Opportunity to lead in one of Australia’s most critical sectors
Sydney CBD location

Contact: ashleyduffy@future-you.com.au

Flexible Hybrid Work Model - Enjoy the freedom to work from home most days.
Extra Time for You - In addition to your annual leave, you'll receive one Leidos Life Day off every month to recharge and focus on what matters most. That's an extra 12 days of leave every year!
Family Friendly Certified - We're proud to be recognised as a Family Friendly Workplace, actively supporting our team members in balancing their professional and personal commitments.
 

Our team feel Leidos is a great place to work. Learn more about our culture and benefits by visiting us here https://www.leidos.com/company/global/australia/careers

 

Do Work That Matters

Leidos Australia delivers IT and airborne solutions that protect and advance the Australian way of life.  Our 2000 local experts, backed by our global experience and network of partners, are working to solve the world's toughest challenges in government, intelligence, defence, aviation, border protection and health markets.

 

Your New Role and Responsibilities

Are you ready to make a meaningful impact across a portfolio of dynamic IT projects? Leidos Australia is seeking a Senior Project Financial Analyst to play a key role in driving financial performance, and supporting strategic decision-making.

In this role, you will:

Act as a strategic business partner to program and project teams, offering financial advice that aligns with operational goals and contractual commitments.

Build and maintain strong relationships with stakeholders across finance, delivery, and operations to ensure alignment and transparency.

Provide decision support through cost analysis, scenario modelling, and risk assessment to enable proactive financial management.

Lead monthly financial reporting and variance analysis, translating data into actionable insights for senior stakeholders.

Support budgeting and forecasting processes by leveraging historical trends and performance metrics to guide planning and resource allocation.

Contribute to continuous improvement by identifying opportunities to enhance financial processes and systems.

This a fantastic opportunity to work in a collaborative environment where your expertise will help shape the success of critical programs.

 

What You'll Bring to Make An Impact

Proven ability to build strong business partnerships and effectively manage a diverse range of stakeholders across functions and geographies.

Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with a proactive approach to navigating competing priorities and driving outcomes under tight deadlines.

Solid foundation in financial management, reporting, and governance, with a track record of supporting project delivery teams and contributing to program success.

Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Office tools, especially Excel, Word, and Outlook, to support data-driven decision-making and reporting.

Experience working in a global business environment is highly valued, particularly with financial systems such as CostPoint, OAC, or OBI.

 

Don't worry if you don't tick all the boxes - if you meet most of them, we encourage you to submit your application.  We're most interested in your strengths, what you want to learn and how far you want to go.

Due to the nature of work we do, this role does require the successful applicant to be an Australian Citizen and eligible to obtain a Baseline Clearance. 

 

Diverse Team Members, Shared Values and a Common Purpose

Providing our customers with smarter solutions takes an incredible team with diversity of thought, experience and perspectives driving innovation. Inclusion is at the heart of our culture and is one of our core values. It's about creating a workplace where everyone can do important work, feels welcome, valued, and respected, and has equal access to opportunities to thrive. Paul Chase - Chief Executive, Leidos Australia.

Leidos Australia is an equal opportunities organisation and is committed to creating a truly inclusive workplace. We welcome and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders, culturally and linguistically diverse people, people with disabilities, veterans, neurodiverse people, and people of all genders, sexualities, and age groups.

Our five Advocacy Groups (Women and Allies Network, Young Professionals, Defence & Emergency Services, Action for Accessibility and Abilities and Pride+) provide an opportunity for team members to connect and collaborate on shared interests, and work to support and celebrate our diverse community.

Next Steps

To apply for this role, follow the links or apply via our Careers page.  
Recruitment process - 1 - 2 interviews (in person) & background checks. 
Applicants may also need to meet International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) requirements. In certain circumstances this can place limitations on persons who hold dual nationality, permanent residency or are former nationals of certain countries as per ITAR 126.1. 
We are committed to making our recruitment process accessible to all candidates. Please contact our Careers team careers.au@au.leidos.com if you'd like to discuss any additional support during your application or throughout the recruitment process.

Job Title: Data & Analytics Lead - Snowflake, Airflow, DBT
Ad Text:
The Organisation:
A leading & growing Retail organisation based in Sydney is seeking a dynamic and hands-on data & analytics leader to execute and be accountable for their existing data strategy and delivery of end-to-end data solutions that will be critical in enabling data-driven decision making. This role is hybrid with a minimum of 3 days in the office.

Key Priorities of the Role:

Strong business partnering with leaders across the organisation to understand their requirements  and translate into innovative data solutions.
Hands-on delivery of these data solutions, ensuring adherence to best practices whilst overseeing a small data internal and external data team.
Leverage your ability to apply vision and big-picture thinking with your expertise in technical delivery of secure, scalable and high-quality data & analytics solutions.
Apply & develop your knowledge of emerging technologies and AI tools such as Claude, Snowflake Cortex, NLPs, LLMs & automation.
Collaborate with data engineering, architecture & reporting colleagues to design, develop and implement these solutions whilst providing mentorship & guidance towards continuous improvement and knowledge sharing.
Build strong working relationships both internally and externally, including vendor management.

Your Skillset:

Demonstrated experience in leading a small data team whilst remaining hands-on in design & development of data solutions (50-50).
Strong data engineering background with progression into leading a team.
Hands-on experience in Snowflake DWH, SQL (SSAS), Airflow, DBT, Python, CI/CD, Power BI.
AI tools such as Claude, Snowflake Cortex & ML & NLPs.
Data lake architecture, strong multi-dimensional data modeling, real-time data streaming & EDD.
Enjoy business partnering with key stakeholders and C-Suite - become a trusted advisor to multiple business & operational teams.
Passion for continuous improvement & open to new tools & technologies.
Collaborative and mentoring leadership style.
Retail or FMCG experience desirable.

You must have Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency to be considered for this role and be Sydney based.

Please apply below for immediate consideration.

Company Description


Turner & Townsend is a global professional services company with over 22,000 people in more than 62 countries.

Working with our clients across real estate, infrastructure, energy and natural resources, we transform together delivering outcomes that improve people’s lives. Working in partnership makes it possible to deliver the world’s most impactful projects and programmes as we turn challenge into opportunity and complexity into success.

Our capabilities include programme, project, cost, asset and commercial management, controls and performance, procurement and supply chain, net zero and digital solutions.

We are majority-owned by CBRE Group, Inc., the world’s largest commercial real estate services and investment firm, with our partners holding a significant minority interest. Turner & Townsend and CBRE work together to provide clients with the premier programme, project and cost management offering in markets around the world.

Please visit our website: www.turnerandtownsend.com

Job Description


We are seeking an exceptional Associate Director to drive growth in the market, lead strategic client relationships, and help us achieve our ambitious growth targets over the coming years. Due to increasing demand for our Infrastructure Digital – Data and Analytics services, this role will play a critical part in expanding our capabilities and delivering data excellence across our team and client engagements. We are looking for a commercially and technically minded leader with a proven track record of delivering successful data-driven solutions. The ideal candidate will be skilled in managing relationships and providing technical guidance across a multidisciplinary team spanning data visualisation, automation, infrastructure, data science, and systems implementation.

The Role

As the Associate Director, your responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Leverage a strong technical background to effectively engage with both clients and technical teams.
Lead client engagements, define delivery strategies, and provide technical assurance across complex data and analytics projects.
Manage and deliver system deployments across critical PMO functions, including cost control, schedule management, and risk mitigation.
Design, develop, and implement data-driven solutions in collaboration with clients and internal teams to generate actionable insights and enhance performance.
Produce comprehensive design documentation and technical specifications, including functional and non-functional requirements and end-to-end data processes.
Lead and contribute to business development initiatives, including the preparation of proposals and client presentations.
Cultivate new client relationships while maintaining and strengthening existing partnerships.
Oversee the development and deployment of data systems and pipelines, ensuring data quality and resolving any related issues.
Collaborate effectively within multidisciplinary teams to deliver integrated solutions.
Create high-quality communications, reports, and presentations tailored to diverse audiences.
Champion innovation and growth by mentoring team members and fostering an inclusive, high-performance culture.
Contribute to the development and continuous improvement of internal documentation, processes, and knowledge-sharing practices.

Qualifications


Essential Skills:

Proven experience implementing data reporting and dashboarding solutions
Experience with Agile delivery methodologies
Hands-on experience designing or implementing data architecture, particularly within the Azure data stack
Proficiency in analytics languages such as SQL or Python
A strong understanding of Project and Program management tools e.g. EcoSys/Contruent/Planview/Planisware/ InEIght/ Oracle Aconex/ Unifier
Exceptional communication skills – able to translate complex technical concepts for diverse audiences

Desirable Skills:

Experience with unit testing, integration testing, system testing, and user acceptance testing
Familiarity with data science approaches and best practices
Experience translating Azure data solution designs into actionable implementations
Background in requirements gathering, solution design, and implementation of data platforms
Experience working in multi-disciplinary teams (e.g., software engineers, DevOps, infrastructure, data scientists)
Exposure to Digital Twin, BIM and Internet of Things (IoT) solutions

System Knowledge:

Business Intelligence
Power BI / Tableau or similar 
 
Programming
Python / R Data or similar 
MS Visual Studio or similar 
MS365 Power Platform 
 
Database Platform Development
EcoSys / Contruent / Planview / Planisware / InEIght / Oracle Aconex / Unifier
Microsoft SQL + SSMS 
Microsoft Azure Platform (Synapse, Machine Learning, Databricks)

Additional Information


Our inspired people share our vision and mission. We provide a great place to work, where each person has the opportunity and voice to affect change.

We want our people to succeed both in work and life. To support this we promote a healthy, productive and flexible working environment that respects work-life balance. 

Turner & Townsend is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees and actively encourage applications from all sectors of the community.

Please find out more about us at www.turnerandtownsend.com/
